---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="projects">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-5">Projects</h2>
  <div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Deep Learning for Climate Downscaling</h3>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-12">
      <p class="text-slate-700 max-w-1/3 mb-2">
        This summer I'm taking part in a research internship at the University
        of Glasgow. In which, I will be making deep learning models that peform
        climate downscaling. The main goal will be devloping a CNN model that
        follows physical constraints (such as conservation of mass etc), and to
        utilise self supervised learning and transfer learning to create better
        kernels.
      </p>
      <img
        src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}images/climate.png`}
        alt="photo of what climate downscaling is"
        class="object-scale-down w-1/4 h-auto display:inline"
      />
    </div>
    <a href="#" class="text-zinc hover:text-green-300">Check out repo.</a>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-5">No Mouse No Problem</h3>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-12">
      <p class="text-slate-700 max-w-1/3 mb-2">
        This project utilises OpenCV and MediaPipe to allow the user to navigate
        their computer with hand gestures. This was made just for a bit of fun,
        hence the actual usability of it and overall look etc is not very
        polished. I may implement an actual UI for it at some point to make it
        more professional.
      </p>
    </div>
    <a href="#" class="text-zinc hover:text-green-300">Check out repo.</a>
  </div>
</Layout>
